In the Role 
As a Business Intelligence Analyst with Amplio, you will be responsible for delivering outstanding data visualization solutions for our revenue operations team. The ideal candidate will have extensive knowledge of data visualization, data manipulation, data storytelling, and business intelligence best practices, along with full project lifecycle experience on multiple projects deployed using Tableau or PowerBI 
Core Responsibilities: 
Use internal & external data to identify KPIs, define data structures, and design/build new reports and dashboards in Tableau 
Query data and build views/tables leveraging best practices for BI data structures 
Leverage data visualization best practices to build dashboards based on the requirements and business use cases identified during internal discovery meetings 
Quickly iterate on design of dashboards incorporating feedback from the project and internal teams 
Translate data into actionable insights and stories which drive change in operations strategy and tactics 
Requirements:
 
 Bachelorâ€™s Degree (Statistics, Economics or related quantitative field preferred); advanced degree is a plus 
3-5 years of experience building dashboards and delivering insights using Tableau 
Tableau proficiency with experience performing front-end maintenance including setting permissions, defining user groups, and other user/content admin tasks 
Experience with additional BI/data visualization tools 
Intermediate SQL experience to conduct basic queries for data analysis and use case analysis; Experience with data modeling for BI a plus; ETL experience a plus 
Qualified individuals possess excellent communication, interpersonal skills with a strong analytical and problem-solving skills 
At this time we unable to offer H1B sponsorship opportunities. 
